Female abdomen (
Fig. 84
):

Sclerites rectangular, virtually undifferentiated from surrounding membrane; tergites with posterior row and one or two median rows of setae; sternites with uniformly scattered setae; no discernible trichoid sensilla. Ovipositor protractible, about 3.5 as long as sternite 7. Cerci large, setose and setulose, ventral and apical areas with numerous thicker, blunt sensory setae ending in apical pore (
Fig. 77
).
